  garden: {
    accumulation: {title:"日积月累",titleEn:"Accumulation",content:{cn:"嫦娥\n[唐] 李商隐\n云母屏风烛影深，\n长河渐落晓星沉。\n嫦娥应悔偷灵药，\n碧海青天夜夜心。",en:"Chang\u2019e\nby Li Shangyin (Tang)\nBehind the mica screen, candle shadows deepen;\nthe Milky Way sinks, the dawn star fades.\nChang\u2019e must regret stealing the elixir \u2014\nblue sea, clear sky, lonely heart night after night."}},
    wordSentence: {title:"词句段运用",titleEn:"Word & Sentence Practice",content:{cn:"说说下面的词语让你想到了哪些人物或故事：腾云驾雾、上天入地、神机妙算、各显神通、三头六臂、神通广大、未卜先知、刀枪不入",en:"Which characters or stories do these words bring to mind: cloud-riding, heaven-and-earth-spanning, divine strategy, each showing powers, three heads six arms, great magic, foresight, invulnerable"}},
    composition: {title:"习作",titleEn:"Composition",prompt:{cn:"我和____过一天：如果有机会和神话或童话人物中的某一位过上一天，你会选择谁？你们会一起去哪里？会做些什么？",en:"A Day with ____: If you could spend a day with any mythical or fairy tale character, who would you choose? Where would you go and what would you do?"},modelEssays:[
      {title:"我和孙悟空过一天",titleEn:"A Day with Sun Wukong",level:"基础",
        structure:[
          {cn:"开头：说明遇到孙悟空的情景",en:"Opening: describe how you met Sun Wukong"},
          {cn:"中间：和孙悟空一起做的事情",en:"Body: things you did together with Sun Wukong"},
          {cn:"结尾：告别和感受",en:"Ending: farewell and feelings"}
        ],
        cn:"今天早上，我刚睁开眼睛，就看到一个身穿虎皮裙、手拿金箍棒的人站在我的床前。我揉了揉眼睛，天哪，竟然是孙悟空！\n\u201C小朋友，俺老孙今天带你玩一天，走不走？\u201D孙悟空笑嘻嘻地说。我高兴得一下子从床上跳了起来：\u201C走走走！\u201D\n孙悟空拔下一根毫毛，轻轻一吹，变出了一朵筋斗云。我坐在软绵绵的云朵上，\u201C嗖\u201D的一下飞上了天空。从天上往下看，房子变得像火柴盒那么小，马路像一条条丝带，真是太壮观了！\n我们先飞到了大海边。孙悟空带我去了东海龙宫。海底的世界五颜六色，到处是珊瑚和水母，还有成群结队的热带鱼游来游去。龙王请我们吃了一顿丰盛的海鲜大餐，味道好极了。\n接着，孙悟空又带我飞到了花果山。水帘洞里住着好多小猴子，它们围着我又跳又叫，还摘了好多桃子给我吃。山上的桃子又大又甜，比我在超市买的好吃多了。\n太阳快落山了，孙悟空把我送回了家。\u201C小朋友，下次再来找俺老孙玩！\u201D说完，他一个筋斗翻进了云里，不见了。\n今天真是太开心了！我希望孙悟空还能再来找我玩。",
        en:"This morning, the moment I opened my eyes, I saw someone wearing a tiger-skin skirt and holding a golden staff standing by my bed. I rubbed my eyes — oh my, it was Sun Wukong!\n'Little friend, Old Sun will take you out to play today. Coming?' Sun Wukong said with a grin. I jumped out of bed excitedly: 'Yes, yes, yes!'\nSun Wukong plucked a hair and blew on it gently, creating a somersault cloud. I sat on the soft, fluffy cloud and — whoosh — flew up into the sky. Looking down from above, houses looked as small as matchboxes and roads looked like ribbons. It was spectacular!\nFirst, we flew to the seaside. Sun Wukong took me to the Dragon King's Palace in the East Sea. The underwater world was colorful, with coral and jellyfish everywhere, and schools of tropical fish swimming about. The Dragon King treated us to a lavish seafood feast that tasted amazing.\nNext, Sun Wukong flew me to Flower-Fruit Mountain. The Water Curtain Cave was home to many little monkeys who jumped and chattered around me, picking lots of peaches for me to eat. The mountain peaches were big and sweet, much tastier than anything from the supermarket.\nAs the sun was setting, Sun Wukong brought me home. 'Little friend, come find Old Sun again next time!' he said, then did a somersault into the clouds and disappeared.\nToday was so much fun! I hope Sun Wukong will come play with me again.",
        notes:"文章想象合理，以孙悟空的经典本领（筋斗云、变化）为线索，安排了两个游玩地点（龙宫和花果山），都是《西游记》中的经典场景。结构清晰，按时间顺序叙述。语言简洁明快，适合基础水平。",
        notesEn:"The imagination is reasonable, using Sun Wukong's classic abilities (somersault cloud, transformation) as a thread, arranging two locations (Dragon Palace and Flower-Fruit Mountain) that are iconic settings from Journey to the West. The structure is clear with chronological narration. The language is concise and lively, suitable for basic level."},
      {title:"我和哪吒过一天",titleEn:"A Day with Nezha",level:"提高",
        structure:[
          {cn:"开头：穿越式开头，交代相遇",en:"Opening: time-travel opening, explain the meeting"},
          {cn:"中间：一起冒险，解决问题",en:"Body: adventure together, solve a problem"},
          {cn:"展现人物性格",en:"Show character personality"},
          {cn:"结尾：感悟友谊和勇气",en:"Ending: reflect on friendship and courage"}
        ],
        cn:"一阵奇怪的风吹过，我眼前一亮，发现自己竟然站在一片波涛汹涌的海边。一个脚踩风火轮、手持火尖枪的少年从天上飞了下来，冲我喊道：\u201C嘿，你是谁？怎么到这里来了？\u201D\n我吓了一跳，定睛一看——这不是哪吒吗？那个脚踩风火轮的三太子！\n\u201C你来得正好！\u201D哪吒着急地说，\u201C下游的村子发了大洪水，老百姓都被困在屋顶上了，你愿不愿意跟我去救人？\u201D\n我虽然害怕，但还是用力地点了点头。哪吒把混天绫绑在我腰上，带着我飞了起来。风火轮的速度快极了，耳边的风呼呼作响，我紧紧抓住哪吒的胳膊，不敢往下看。\n到了村子上空，我看到洪水已经淹没了大半个村庄。有几个老人和孩子站在屋顶上，焦急地向天空挥手。哪吒二话不说，把火尖枪往地上一插，一股神力涌出，在洪水中开辟出了一条通道。他让我站在高处，负责接应，自己则飞下去把被困的人一个个背到安全的地方。\n有个小女孩吓得哇哇大哭，不肯松开屋顶的柱子。哪吒轻轻拍了拍她的肩膀，微笑着说：\u201C别怕，有我在，没人能伤害你。\u201D小女孩这才慢慢松开了手。\n洪水退去后，村民们纷纷向哪吒道谢。哪吒却摆摆手说：\u201C不用谢，保护老百姓是我该做的。\u201D说完，他看了看我，竖起大拇指：\u201C你也很勇敢，以后你就是我的朋友了！\u201D\n回到家后，我心里一直暖暖的。原来勇敢不是不害怕，而是害怕了还愿意站出来。谢谢你，哪吒，你教会了我什么是真正的勇气。",
        en:"A strange wind blew past, and suddenly I found myself standing on a shore with surging waves. A boy riding Wind-Fire Wheels and wielding a Fire-Tipped Spear flew down from the sky and shouted at me, 'Hey, who are you? How did you get here?'\nI was startled, but looking carefully — it was Nezha! The Third Prince on his Wind-Fire Wheels!\n'You came at the right time!' Nezha said urgently. 'The village downstream is flooded, and the people are trapped on their rooftops. Will you come help me rescue them?'\nAlthough I was scared, I nodded firmly. Nezha tied his Red Armillary Sash around my waist and flew up with me. The Wind-Fire Wheels were incredibly fast, the wind howling in my ears. I clung tightly to Nezha's arm, not daring to look down.\nAbove the village, I saw that the floodwater had submerged most of it. Several elderly people and children stood on rooftops, anxiously waving at the sky. Without hesitation, Nezha thrust his spear into the ground, and a divine force surged out, carving a channel through the floodwater. He had me stand on high ground to receive people while he flew down and carried the trapped villagers to safety one by one.\nA little girl was crying and wouldn't let go of a rooftop pillar. Nezha gently patted her shoulder and smiled, 'Don't be afraid. With me here, no one can hurt you.' Only then did the girl slowly loosen her grip.\nAfter the flood receded, the villagers thanked Nezha profusely. But he just waved his hand and said, 'No need to thank me. Protecting the people is my duty.' Then he looked at me and gave a thumbs up: 'You were brave too. From now on, you're my friend!'\nBack home, my heart felt warm for a long time. It turns out courage isn't about not being afraid — it's about being willing to step forward even when you are afraid. Thank you, Nezha. You taught me what true courage means.",
        notes:"本文想象丰富又合理。选择哪吒作为同行者，安排了一个\u201C抗洪救人\u201D的故事情节，很有正能量。文中既展现了哪吒的英勇善良，也写出了\u201C我\u201D从害怕到勇敢的心理变化。哪吒安慰小女孩的细节体现了他的温柔一面。结尾的感悟\u201C勇敢不是不害怕，而是害怕了还愿意站出来\u201D非常精彩，有深度。",
        notesEn:"This essay has rich yet reasonable imagination. Choosing Nezha and creating a flood rescue storyline is very positive. It shows both Nezha's bravery and kindness, and the writer's psychological change from fear to courage. The detail of Nezha comforting the little girl shows his gentle side. The closing insight — 'courage isn't about not being afraid, but being willing to step forward even when afraid' — is excellent and deep."},
      {title:"我和嫦娥过一天",titleEn:"A Day with Chang'e",level:"拓展",
        structure:[
          {cn:"开头：诗意开场，营造梦幻氛围",en:"Opening: poetic start, create a dreamlike atmosphere"},
          {cn:"中间：月宫见闻，融入传说元素",en:"Body: Moon Palace sights, weave in legend elements"},
          {cn:"内心对话，探讨孤独与选择",en:"Inner dialogue, explore loneliness and choices"},
          {cn:"结尾：带着思考回到现实",en:"Ending: return to reality with reflection"}
        ],
        cn:"中秋节的夜晚，月亮又大又圆。我坐在阳台上，对着月亮发呆。忽然，一道银白色的光柱从月亮上直射下来，落在我的脚边。一个身穿白纱、怀抱玉兔的女子飘然而至，对我微笑着说：\u201C月宫太寂寞了，你愿意陪我过一天吗？\u201D\n我踏上光柱，像坐电梯一样，\u201C嗖\u201D地飞到了月亮上。\n月宫比我想象的更加美丽。宫殿是用白玉砌成的，在月光下泛着柔和的光芒。院子里有一棵巨大的桂花树，金色的桂花缀满枝头，香气浓郁，一阵风吹过，桂花纷纷扬扬地飘落下来，像下了一场金色的雨。\n\u201C这棵桂树已经长了三千年了，\u201D嫦娥轻声说，\u201C每到秋天，它就开满了花。可惜，没有人和我一起赏花。\u201D她的声音里带着一丝淡淡的忧伤。\n我跟着嫦娥在月宫里参观。她带我看了吴刚伐桂——吴刚挥着斧子用力砍桂树，可是砍出的伤口马上就愈合了。吴刚擦了擦汗，无奈地笑了笑。嫦娥还带我去了她的书房，里面摆满了古老的竹简。\u201C这些都是我在月宫里写的诗，\u201D她翻开一卷竹简，上面写着：\u201C独坐广寒宫，遥望人间灯。但愿人长久，千里共婵娟。\u201D\n\u201C你不想回到人间去吗？\u201D我忍不住问。\n嫦娥沉默了一会儿，然后微微一笑：\u201C每个选择都有代价。我选择了长生不老，却失去了人间的温暖。\u201D她低头抚摸着怀中的玉兔，\u201C如果再让我选一次，我也许会选择做一个普通人。普通人虽然会老、会离别，但至少有家人在身边，有热闹的日子可以过。\u201D\n夜深了，嫦娥送我回到人间。临别时，她递给我一枝桂花：\u201C替我问候人间的人们。\u201D\n我回到阳台上，手里真的多了一枝桂花。抬头望月，我似乎看到嫦娥在月宫的窗前，对着人间微笑。那一刻，我突然明白了：幸福不在天上，不在长生不老里，而在我们每一天平凡而温暖的生活中。",
        en:"On Mid-Autumn night, the moon was big and round. I sat on the balcony, gazing at it in a daze. Suddenly, a beam of silver-white light shot down from the moon and landed at my feet. A woman in white gauze, cradling a jade rabbit, floated down gracefully and smiled at me: 'The Moon Palace is too lonely. Would you like to keep me company for a day?'\nI stepped onto the beam of light and — whoosh — flew up to the moon like riding an elevator.\nThe Moon Palace was more beautiful than I had imagined. The palace was built from white jade, glowing softly in the moonlight. In the courtyard stood a massive osmanthus tree, its golden blossoms dotting every branch, filling the air with rich fragrance. A breeze sent the flowers drifting down like a golden rain.\n'This tree has been growing for three thousand years,' Chang'e said softly. 'Every autumn it blooms fully. But sadly, there's no one to enjoy the flowers with me.' Her voice carried a faint trace of sadness.\nI followed Chang'e on a tour of the Moon Palace. She showed me Wu Gang chopping the osmanthus tree — he swung his axe with great force, but the wound healed instantly. Wu Gang wiped his sweat and smiled helplessly. Chang'e also took me to her study, filled with ancient bamboo scrolls. 'These are all poems I wrote in the Moon Palace,' she said, unrolling one scroll that read: 'Sitting alone in the Vast Cold Palace, gazing at the lights of the human world. May people live long, sharing this bright moon across a thousand miles.'\n'Don't you want to return to the human world?' I couldn't help asking.\nChang'e was silent for a moment, then smiled gently: 'Every choice has a price. I chose immortality but lost the warmth of the human world.' She looked down and stroked the jade rabbit in her arms. 'If I could choose again, perhaps I would choose to be an ordinary person. Ordinary people grow old and face partings, but at least they have family by their side and lively days to live.'\nLate at night, Chang'e sent me back to the human world. Before parting, she handed me a sprig of osmanthus: 'Send my greetings to the people of the world.'\nBack on my balcony, I really did have an extra sprig of osmanthus in my hand. Looking up at the moon, I seemed to see Chang'e at the Moon Palace window, smiling at the human world. In that moment, I suddenly understood: happiness is not in the heavens, not in immortality, but in our ordinary, warm, everyday lives.",
        notes:"本文最大的特色是将想象与思考融为一体。不仅写了月宫的见闻（桂花树、吴刚伐桂、书房竹简），还通过与嫦娥的对话探讨了一个深刻的话题——选择与代价。嫦娥\u201C如果再选一次会选做普通人\u201D的感慨令人动容。全文氛围诗意唯美，用了大量优美的意象（银白色光柱、金色桂花雨、白玉宫殿）。结尾的感悟\u201C幸福在平凡而温暖的生活中\u201D既扣住了主题，又有哲理深度，达到了四年级作文的较高水平。",
        notesEn:"The biggest feature is blending imagination with reflection. Beyond describing Moon Palace sights (osmanthus tree, Wu Gang chopping, bamboo scrolls), it uses dialogue with Chang'e to explore a profound topic — choices and their costs. Chang'e's sentiment that 'if I could choose again, I'd be an ordinary person' is deeply touching. The atmosphere is poetic and beautiful throughout, with rich imagery (silver beam, golden flower rain, jade palace). The closing insight — 'happiness is in our ordinary, warm everyday lives' — ties the theme together with philosophical depth, reaching a high standard for Grade 4 composition."}
    ]}
  }
