      textEn: [
        "Everyone said: a cow\u2019s eyes make people look bigger than the cow, so cows fear people; a goose\u2019s eyes make people look smaller, so geese don\u2019t fear people.",
        "We totally believed this. We were not at all afraid of cows \u2014 we dared to pat their backs, rub their bellies, even poke them with sticks! The cow just blinked and flicked its tail. Some kids even grabbed the horns, made the cow kneel, and rode its back. I wasn\u2019t that brave, but I dared to thump the cow\u2019s back with my fist.",
        "Geese were a completely different story. We\u2019d stand far away before daring to look at one. If we met geese on the road, we had to make a big detour.",
        "One time, on our way home from school, we walked past the pond and saw four big white geese swimming near the shore. We immediately stopped talking and crept along the wall, trying to pass quietly. Just then, a mischievous boy deliberately tried to lure them over, calling out \u201Cyoo-lee-lee-lee!\u201D The geese heard him, raised their heads, looked at us sideways, and actually climbed up onto the bank. They waddled toward us proudly, stretching their necks, honking loudly, flapping their big wings, as if in their eyes we people simply did not exist.",
        "The children cried out in alarm and fled in a panic. The geese chased even faster. I was so frightened my legs went weak, and I couldn\u2019t run fast at all. Just then, the lead gander came running over with a pitter-patter of feet. Honk honk \u2014 it caught up with me. Honk honk \u2014 it opened its beak and in one bite clamped onto the front of my shirt at my chest, pulling me and refusing to let go. In the chaos, my schoolbag fell and my shoes came off. I thought it was surely going to bite me to death. Perhaps my crying enraged this old gander even more. It used all its strength to drag me, peck me, and flap its wings to beat me.",
        "Just at that moment, a small boat paddled over from the pond, and Uncle Jinkui the fisherman jumped from the boat onto the bank and came over quickly. Uncle Jinkui was a sturdy fellow. In one grab, he seized the goose\u2019s long neck. The goose scratched him with its claws and pecked him with its beak. But Uncle Jinkui\u2019s strength was so great \u2014 he lightly lifted the goose, and then, just like flinging a wine bottle, with a whoosh, he hurled the old gander into midair. It spread its wings and splashed down into the pond. At this, the other three geese were frightened too. One after another they spread their wings, jumped into the pond, and swam away into the distance.",
        "Uncle Jinkui helped me with my shoes, picked up my bag, ruffled my hair, and said: \u201CWhat\u2019s scary about a goose? Look at you!\u201D I said: \u201CBecause the goose sees us as smaller!\u201D He said: \u201CLet it think so! But if it tries to bully us, we won\u2019t stand for it \u2014 grab its neck and toss it in the pond. Remember, Lin-ge, don\u2019t be afraid of geese.\u201D",
        "I remembered his words and was never afraid of geese again. What\u2019s there to fear? Even if they see us as small, we\u2019re actually stronger! And I stopped picking on cows for no reason either \u2014 just because they see us as big, why should we bully them?"
      ],
